{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"2bd97f25-8b05-4cf5-ad27-44e9bd203170","content":"Here's what needs to change:\n\n1. **Remove** the old assembly reference to `Microsoft.VisualStudio.QualityTools.UnitTestFramework`\n2. **Replace** `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` with the single unified `MSTest` v3 package (it bundles the test SDK, framework, and adapter)\n\nYour test code (`[TestClass]`, `[TestMethod]`, `Assert.*`, `[Timeout]`) is fully compatible — no C# changes needed.","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_014mcoypNfTWEE8bSStK8TWm","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Upgrading to MSTest v3"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01EtiZZfZgudGbeThXdFV1QV","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-a5aab6a279f04671acc7550378f004e1/TestProject.csproj","old_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Reference Include=\"Microsoft.VisualStudio.QualityTools.UnitTestFramework\" />\n  </ItemGroup>\n\n  <ItemGroup>\n    <PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk\" Version=\"17.5.0\" />\n  </ItemGroup>","new_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <PackageReference Include=\"MSTest\" Version=\"3.8.3\" />\n  </ItemGroup>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-a5aab6a279f04671acc7550378f004e1/TestProject.csproj."}],"interactionId":"9d82ffa5-5463-47a0-b3ff-1283a8ae623a","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to upgrade to MSTest v3. Here's what needs to change:\n\n1. **Remove the old assembly reference** to `Microsoft.VisualStudio.QualityTools.UnitTestFramework`\n2. **Add the MSTest v3 NuGet package** — MSTest v3 consolidated everything into a single `MSTest` package (replacing `MSTest.TestFramework` + `MSTest.TestAdapter`)\n3. **Update `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk`** to a newer version\n4. **Update the target framework** — MSTest v3 doesn't support .NET Framework 4.6.2 directly (minimum is net462 but they recommend upgrading). Actually, let me check — MSTest v3 supports .NET Framework 4.6.2+, so net462 should be fine.\n\n\n5. The existi